              I highly value privacy and security and care about social and
              environmental impact. Current AI developments are promising but I'm also
              guarded regarding consequences and usecase(s): I do not consider it as a
              solution to everything.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
              TDD, CI/CD and DevOps are things I like to implement and automate with
              tools such as <a href="https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/">Pytest</a>,
              <a href="https://playwright.dev/">Playwright</a>,
              <a href="https://www.docker.com/">Docker</a> /
              <a href="https://podman.io/">Podman</a>,
              <a href="https://docs.gitlab.com/ci/">GitLab CI/CD</a> and
              <a href="https://github.com/features/actions">Github Actions</a>. I
              sometimes orchestrate full stacks with
              <a href="https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform">Terraform</a> and/or
              <a href="https://docs.ansible.com/">Ansible</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
              I'm also familiar with front-end development including HTML, Javascript
              (TS), (S)CSS or frameworks like
              <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/">tailwindcss</a> and
              <a href="https://vuejs.org/">Vue.js</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-justify">
              Unix based systems like Linux and MacOS are my preferred OS's. My current
              favourite Container OS is
              <a href="https://alpinelinux.org/">Alpine Linux</a>: A lean linux
              distribution with a small footprint.
              <a href="https://www.sublimetext.com/">Sublime Text</a> is still my
              favourite editor.
            </p>
